<h2 id="section-top">Weight loss services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=818">Liverpool University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address">Aintree LOSS weight management service, Aintree University Hospital, Aintree Hall, Longmoor Lane, Liverpool, L9 7AL<br/>0151 529 3351</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent08b0fa5609d64fbf8bee85f10afab589">
</div>
<p>Aintree LOSS (Liverpool Obesity Support Service) is an NHS weight management programme for people with obesity - with a BMI (Body Mass Index) of 40 or above or a BMI of 35 or above with weight related health problems such as diabetes.</p>
<p>The service is available for adults (over 18) who are registered with a Liverpool PCT GP practice.</p>
<p>Individuals should discuss with their GP to find out if they are able to join Aintree LOSS.</p>
<p>The service offers a two year programme which includes an initial assessment with a GP who has an interest in obesity.Â  This is followed by a tailored programme which may include individual and/ or group appointments with dietitians, physiotherapists, psychotherapists and Health Care Support Workers.</p>
<p>The focus is on a long term approach to sustainable weight loss and to support individuals to make realistic and achievable lifestyle changes.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-thingsshouldknowmodule">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Things you should know</h3>
<p>More information about the Aintree LOSS service can be found here: http://www.aintreehospitals.nhs.uk/weight_management/Aintree_LOSS.asp</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
